The paper proposes two efficient epidemic spreading algorithms for arbitrary network structures, based on the SIR compartment model. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures and probability distributions, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of empirical complex networks, which could suggest it belongs to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Machine Learning (cs.MA).
